Distraction: creating an n x n autocorrelation matrix based on a correlation rho in #rstats: 
n <- 5
rho <- 0.9
mat <- diag(n)
mat <- rho^abs(row(mat) - col(mat)) https://t.co/jmPWw51irW

Then abs(row(mat) - col(mat)) is telling us how far is each location from the diagonal.

We use that distance as an exponent for rho (0.9 in our example).
